                    <p class="text-dark" style="line-height:1" >Uzbekistan’s unique history, culture and natural wonders draws visitors from around the world.</p>

                    <p class="text-dark" style="line-height:1" >At Chortoq travels we have curated the most exciting educational trips in the heart of Uzbekistan from history to culture, nature and culinary tours. Our unprecedented access to unique places, top guides, educational tour leaders, brilliantly detailed itineraries, stays in local hotels and, most importantly, amazing experiences, make us the perfect choice for travellers.</p>

                    <p class="text-dark" style="line-height:1" >Depending on the time of year, Uzbekistan is either a glorious explosion of emerald green valleys or ethereally blue waters or wind-thrashed deserts or magical frozen mountains. Let is breath-taking natural beauty of the country astound you and the magic of the ancient cities enchant you.</p>

                    <p class="text-dark" style="line-height:1" >Embark on a nature-fuelled trip around its otherworldly, spectacular forests and mysterious mountain regions inhabited by some of the most extraordinary creatures and dotted with hilltop villages, untouched by modern life. Get up close to the famous local wildlife and enjoy the stunning scenery along with unique adventures and gourmet tours.</p>

                     <p class="text-dark" style="line-height:1" >Explore the beautifully preserved ancient monuments and historic towns and titled cities of Tashkent, Samarkand, Bukhara and Khiva that tell the 5,000-year-old tale of the Silk Road. Discover the country’s antique wonders, UNESCO World Heritage sites and archaeological treasures visiting its magnificent mosques, madrassas, caravanserais and mausolea with skys-craping turquoise minarets. Walk in the footsteps of travellers, traders, scholars and conquerors.</p>

                    <p class="text-dark" style="line-height:1" >Famous for its culinary brilliance and warm hospitality, each region in Uzbekistan makes for a perfect food-lover’s getaway and boasts its own distinct version of ‘plov’ (a rice dish with stewed meat and vegetables) and ‘non’ (bread) that are accompanied by fresh tomato salad. </p>
                    <p class="text-dark" style="line-height:1" >On the menu are a variety of delicious soups and meat dishes such as manti, shurpa, shashlik, lagman, samsa, dimlama, buglama, mastava prepared by highly skilled chefs and accompanied by haunting music of dombra and tambur and fine regional wines, beers, vodka and other beverages. The traditional teahouses (chaikhanas) are extremely popular across the country and are culturally very significant. Delight your taste buds and enjoy a holiday with a difference. </p>

                     <p class="text-dark" style="line-height:1" >The lively bazaars in Uzbekistan are equally enthralling – full of beautiful pure cotton and silk textiles (Ikat and suzani), embroidered tapestries, fascinating handicrafts, ceramics, teapots, urns, intricate silver ornaments, silk carpets and spices. </p>

                       <p class="text-dark" style="line-height:1" >A tailor-made tour can be created for you or a group by our Chortoq travels experts based on your schedule, style and interests. </p>
